  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and analyse costing for tenders.</li>\n  <li>Prepare, compile and submit progress claim in timely manner including updating payment records.</li>\n  <li>Check &amp; prepare progress payment certificates for all sub-contractors including site valuations with supervisors.</li>\n  <li>Prepare document for inviting quotations, prepare comparison, tender report.</li>\n  <li>Be involved in pre and post contract administration duties including debit notes for back-charges, purchases on behalf of sub-contractors, variations, finalize sub accounts in the period of final measurement.</li>\n  <li>Perform risk and value management and cost control.</li>\n  <li>Prepare cost estimation, quantity take-off for materials procurement, cost evaluations, pre-qualification of sub-contractors.</li>\n  <li>Assist in contractual matters such as extension of time, contractual correspondences, etc;</li>\n  <li>Liaise with main contractors, sub-contractors, clients, project team, in-house factories etc.</li>\n  <li>Prepare drawings or details design documents using AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Attend to project &amp; site meetings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma with at least 1 year of experience in Quantity Surveying (MEP), preferably in data centre      or critical environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(ITE holder with relevant years of experience or fresh degree/diploma holder can be considered)</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Knowledge in project management tools, solutions, and techniques an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Certification in workplace safety (eg. WSQ, WSH) preferred.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Authority Requirement and Code of Practice preferred.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication and collaborative skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
